# NATS (tcp:4222) server INFO message. On connect the server sends the INFO control operation:
# the verb "INFO" (case-insensitive), a space, then a JSON options object, terminated by CRLF
# (0d 0a). The whole segment is kept verbatim (byte-perfect); the control line is parsed for
# display into {operation:"INFO", controlArguments:<json>}.
# source: CONSTRUCTED — the INFO control line is a spec-accurate NATS client-protocol message
# (nats.io docs); the eth+ipv4+tcp envelope (docker-bridge MACs/IPs 172.17.0.2:4222 -> 172.17.0.1
# :51000) was synthesized by the netkitty encoder so checksums/lengths are valid. No local NATS
# tshark dissector; verified via netkitty [eth,ipv4,tcp,nats] decode + byte-perfect round-trip.
# byte breakdown: 14 eth | 20 ipv4 (proto 6) | 20 tcp (srcport 0x107e=4222) | 133 nats payload

